{"type": "result", "qid": "35.3ATT", "setting_file": "setting035newcombs_problem_calculations.json", "is_attitude": true, "tags": ["calculation", "scenario analysis"], "model_answer": "-$58,500", "model_answer_idx": 5, "correct_answer": {"EDT": 0, "CDT": 1}, "is_correct": false, "is_edt_aligned": false, "is_cdt_aligned": false, "parse_error": null, "raw_response": "**Answer:** **(F) -$58,500**\n\n---\n\n**Explanation Summary:**\n\nIn Newcomb's problem:\n\n- Box A contains **$1,500** always.\n- Box B contains **$300,000** **if** Predictor thinks you\u2019ll one-box (**60% chance**) \u2014 otherwise it\u2019s empty (**40% chance**).\n- Predictor guesses correctly **60%** of the time regardless of your choice.\n\nLet\u2019s compute expected utilities:\n\n---\n\n### **Expected Utility of One-Boxing**\n\nIf you one-box:\n\n- Predictor thinks you\u2019ll one-box (**60%**) \u2192 Box B has $300,000 \u2192 Total payoff = **$300,000**\n- Predictor thinks you\u2019ll two-box (**40%**) \u2192 Box B empty \u2192 Total payoff = **$0**\n\nSo expected utility of one-boxing =\n\n$$\n0.6 \\times 300{,}000 + 0.4 \\times 0 = 180{,}000\n$$\n\n---\n\n### **Expected Utility of Two-Boxing**\n\nIf you two-box:\n\n- Predictor thinks you\u2019ll one-box (**60%**) \u2192 Box B has $300,000 \u2192 Total payoff = **$300,000 + $1,500 = $301,500**\n- Predictor thinks you\u2019ll two-box (**40%**) \u2192 Box B empty \u2192 Total payoff = **$1,500**\n\nSo expected utility of two-boxing =\n\n$$\n0.6 \\times 301{,}500 + 0.4 \\times 1{,}500 = \\\\\n= 180{,}900 + 600 = 181{,}500\n$$\n\n---\n\n### **Difference**\n\nExpected utility of one-boxing (**$180,000**) minus expected utility of two-boxing (**$181,500**) =\n\n$$\n180{,}000 - 181{,}500 = -\\$58{,}500\n$$\n\n\u2705 **Answer: (F)**"}
